The '''1982 Monte Carlo Open''' (also known as the '''Jacomo Monte Carlo Open''' for sponsorship reasons) was a men's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]] at the [[Monte Carlo Country Club]] in [[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]] that was part of the [[1982 Volvo Grand Prix]] circuit. It was the 76th edition of the tournament and was held from 5 April through 11 April 1982. [[Guillermo Vilas]] won the singles title.
==Champions== ===Singles=== {{main|1982 Monte Carlo Open – Singles}} {{flagicon|ARG}} '''[[Guillermo Vilas]]''' defeated {{flagicon|TCH}} [[Ivan Lendl]], 6–1, 7–6, 6–3
===Doubles=== {{main|1982 Monte Carlo Open – Doubles}} {{flagicon|AUS}} '''[[Peter McNamara]]''' / {{flagicon|AUS}} '''[[Paul McNamee]]''' defeated {{flagicon|AUS}} [[Mark Edmondson]] / {{flagicon|USA}} [[Sherwood Stewart]], 6–7, 7–6, 6–3
