[[Image:Hluz-U34 901.jpg|thumb|right|240px|Steam locomotive MÁV U34.901, currently in use by Historical Logging Switchback Railway. Picture from May 2006]] '''The Historical Logging Switchback Railway''' in Vychylovka (near [[Nová Bystrica]], [[Slovakia]]) is preserved section technically most interesting part of the former [[narrow-gauge]] [[Zig zag (railway)|zig zag]] [[Forest railway|logging railway]] located in [[Kysuce]] and [[Orava (region)|Orava]] region. The railway was closed in 1971 and disassembled, except an 8&nbsp;km section from Chmúra to Tanečník. Currently a 3.6&nbsp;km section is used as a [[heritage railway]] for tourists.
==Vehicles== *Steam locomotive MÁV 2282/1909 (U34.901) – in service *Steam locomotive MÁV 4281/1916 (U45.9) – in service until 1999 *Steam locomotive Kraus Maffei 15791/1940 – out of service *Steam locomotive ČKD 2612/1948 – out of service *Steam locomotive ČKD 1441/1928 – out of service (this is the last locomotive that has gone along the disassembled track in 1972; Until 1990 placed as memorial in depot Žilina).
