'''New Zealand Antarctic Place-Names Committee''' ('''NZ-APC''') is an adjudicating committee established to authorize the naming of features in the [[Ross Dependency]] on the [[Antarctica|Antarctic]] continent. It is composed of the members of the [[New Zealand Geographic Board]] plus selected specialists on Antarctica. This committee works in collaboration with similar place-naming authorities in Australia, Great Britain and the United States to reach concurrence on each decision.<ref name=breisemeister_waugh1965/> The NZ-APC committee was established in 1956.<ref name=evans1968/>
