'''Szymon h. Gozdawa''', also known as Simon was a twelfth century [[Bishop of Płock]], [[Poland]].<ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/ploc0.htm  Diocese of Płock] at GCatholic.org</ref>

He was from the [[Gozdawa coat of arms|Gozdawa]] [[Szlachta|noble family]] and was [[ordained|appointed]] [[bishop]] in 1112 [[anno domini|AD]]. [[Jan Długosz]] says of him that he was very devout and ruled the [[diocese of Płock|diocese]] for 21 years until he died in 1129. He was also mentioned by the [[historian]] [[Gallus Anonymus]].

